Dame.

01:00:53.570 --> 01:00:54.822
Front desk.

01:00:54.905 --> 01:00:56.323
Hello, Chet?

01:00:56.365 --> 01:00:58.283
This is Barton Fink in room 621.

01:00:58.367 --> 01:01:00.327
Could you try a number for me
in Hollywood?

01:01:00.369 --> 01:01:03.372
Slauson 6-4304.

01:01:03.413 --> 01:01:04.998
Right away, sir.

01:01:07.334 --> 01:01:08.794
Pick it up.
Pick it up.

01:01:08.877 --> 01:01:09.795
Hello.

01:01:09.878 --> 01:01:11.296
Audrey, I need help.

01:01:11.380 --> 01:01:13.757
I know I shouldn't be
calling you like this.

01:01:13.841 --> 01:01:16.384
I wouldn't have
if I could see any alternative.

01:01:16.385 --> 01:01:18.762
I'm sorry.
Listen, how are you?

01:01:18.846 --> 01:01:20.305
You doing okay?

01:01:20.389 --> 01:01:21.765
Who is this?

01:01:21.849 --> 01:01:24.268
Barton! I'm sorry.
It's Barton Fink.

01:01:24.351 --> 01:01:27.271
Barton, I'm afraid
it's not a good time.

01:01:27.354 --> 01:01:29.815
I'm sorry.
I just feel like I need...

01:01:29.898 --> 01:01:31.775
I know I shouldn't ask.

01:01:31.859 --> 01:01:34.820
I just need some kind of help.

01:01:34.903 --> 01:01:37.322
I have a deadline tomorrow.

01:01:37.406 --> 01:01:38.782
All right, Barton.

01:01:38.866 --> 01:01:40.826
I'll see if I can slip away.

01:01:40.909 --> 01:01:42.286
Oh, if you could...

01:01:42.369 --> 01:01:44.329
If I can.

01:01:44.413 --> 01:01:46.331
He... He gets jealous.

01:01:46.415 --> 01:01:47.791
I need help, Audrey.

01:01:49.418 --> 01:01:50.794
I'll try to slip out

01:01:50.878 --> 01:01:54.298
if he quiets down, passes out.

01:01:54.381 --> 01:01:56.758
I'm afraid he thinks...

01:01:56.842 --> 01:01:59.803
Well, he said you were
a buffoon, Barton.

01:01:59.887 --> 01:02:00.846
Uh-huh.

01:02:00.929 --> 01:02:02.347
He becomes irrational.

01:02:03.724 --> 01:02:04.765
Uh-huh, uh-huh.

01:02:04.766 --> 01:02:06.226
I'll try and slip away.

01:02:06.268 --> 01:02:08.061
Who is that?

01:02:25.329 --> 01:02:28.290
Audrey, thank you for coming.

01:02:28.373 --> 01:02:29.291
Thank you.

01:02:29.374 --> 01:02:30.374
Hello, Barton.

01:02:30.375 --> 01:02:32.294
I'm sorry to be...

01:02:32.377 --> 01:02:34.922
such a... such a...

01:02:36.381 --> 01:02:37.299
Thank you.

01:02:37.341 --> 01:02:40.093
That's all right, Barton.

01:02:40.177 --> 01:02:42.638
Everything's going to be all right.

01:02:42.721 --> 01:02:44.640
Yes. Thank you.

01:02:44.765 --> 01:02:45.933
Thank you.

01:02:46.016 --> 01:02:48.477
Yes. Thank you.

01:02:50.354 --> 01:02:51.772
How's Bill?

01:02:51.814 --> 01:02:54.817
Oh, he's, uh...

01:02:54.858 --> 01:02:56.318
He drifted off.

01:02:56.360 --> 01:02:58.946
He'll sleep for a while now.

01:03:00.364 --> 01:03:03.033
What is it you have to do exactly?

01:03:03.116 --> 01:03:07.287
Well, I have to come up
with an outline,

01:03:07.329 --> 01:03:09.248
I guess you call it,

01:03:09.331 --> 01:03:12.251
the whole goddamn story,
soup to nuts, three acts,

01:03:12.334 --> 01:03:14.169
the whole goddamn...

01:03:14.253 --> 01:03:15.587
That's all right, Barton.

01:03:15.671 --> 01:03:17.965
You don't have to write
actual scenes.

01:03:18.006 --> 01:03:21.927
No, but the whole goddamn...

01:03:23.345 --> 01:03:25.264
Audrey...

01:03:25.347 --> 01:03:28.600
have you ever read
any of Bill's wrestling scenarios?

01:03:28.684 --> 01:03:31.353
Yes, I'm afraid I have.

01:03:31.436 --> 01:03:34.940
What are they like?
What are they about?

01:03:35.023 --> 01:03:36.775
Well...

01:03:36.859 --> 01:03:40.654
usually they're simple morality tales.

01:03:40.696 --> 01:03:44.283
There's a good wrestler
and a bad wrestler,

01:03:44.366 --> 01:03:46.410
whom he confronts at the end.

01:03:46.493 --> 01:03:48.870
In between, the good wrestler
has a love interest

01:03:48.871 --> 01:03:51.790
or a small child he has to protect.

01:03:51.874 --> 01:03:53.625
Bill would usually make
the good wrestler

01:03:53.709 --> 01:03:56.086
a backwards type or a convict,

01:03:56.170 --> 01:03:59.548
and sometimes, instead of a waif,

01:03:59.631 --> 01:04:03.343
he'd have the wrestler
protecting an idiot man-child.

01:04:03.385 --> 01:04:06.388
The studio always hated that.

01:04:06.471 --> 01:04:09.057
Some of the scripts were so...

01:04:09.141 --> 01:04:10.392
spirited.

01:04:14.605 --> 01:04:18.775
Barton, look,
it's really just a formula.

01:04:18.859 --> 01:04:21.236
You don't have to type
your soul into it.

01:04:21.320 --> 01:04:23.614
We'll invent some names
and a new setting.

01:04:23.697 --> 01:04:25.741
I'll help you.
It won't take any time at all.

01:04:25.824 --> 01:04:28.243
I did it for Bill so many times.

01:04:28.327 --> 01:04:30.245
You did what for Bill?

01:04:30.287 --> 01:04:33.248
Well... this.

01:04:33.332 --> 01:04:36.543
You wrote his scripts for him?

01:04:39.338 --> 01:04:43.592
Well, the basic ideas
were frequently his.

01:04:43.675 --> 01:04:47.262
You wrote Bill's scripts?

01:04:47.346 --> 01:04:49.097
Jesus, you wrote his...

01:04:49.181 --> 01:04:50.974
Well, what about before that?

01:04:51.058 --> 01:04:52.016
Before what?

01:04:52.017 --> 01:04:54.770
Before Bill came to Hollywood.

01:04:54.853 --> 01:04:57.773
Bill was always the author,
so to speak.

01:04:57.856 --> 01:05:00.901
What do you mean, "so to speak"?

01:05:00.984 --> 01:05:04.947
Audrey, how long have you been his...

01:05:04.988 --> 01:05:06.281
secretary?

01:05:06.365 --> 01:05:09.117
Let's concentrate
on our little project.

01:05:09.201 --> 01:05:11.744
I want to know how many
of Bill's books you wrote!

01:05:11.745 --> 01:05:12.995
I want to know!

01:05:12.996 --> 01:05:15.082
Barton, honestly...

01:05:17.918 --> 01:05:19.878
Only the last couple.

01:05:19.962 --> 01:05:21.088
Hah!

01:05:21.129 --> 01:05:25.384
And my input was
mostly editorial, really,

01:05:25.467 --> 01:05:27.177
after he had been drinking.

01:05:27.261 --> 01:05:28.387
I'll bet.

01:05:28.470 --> 01:05:32.349
Jesus, "the grand productive days"!

01:05:32.432 --> 01:05:34.685
What a goddamn phony.

01:05:34.768 --> 01:05:36.353
W.P. Mayhew...

01:05:36.436 --> 01:05:39.106
William goddamn Phony Mayhew!

01:05:39.148 --> 01:05:40.983
All his guff about escape!

01:05:41.066 --> 01:05:44.027
I'll say he escaped!

01:05:45.946 --> 01:05:47.781
We don't have much time.

01:05:51.994 --> 01:05:54.371
It'll be fine.

01:05:54.454 --> 01:05:57.708
Don't judge him, Barton.

01:05:59.001 --> 01:06:02.379
Don't condescend to him.

01:06:02.462 --> 01:06:06.842
I help Bill most
by understanding him,

01:06:06.925 --> 01:06:08.969
by appreciating him.

01:06:10.888 --> 01:06:14.349
We all need understanding, Barton...

01:06:14.391 --> 01:06:17.311
even you tonight.

01:06:17.352 --> 01:06:19.855
It's all you really need.

01:09:30.337 --> 01:09:32.171
Aah!

01:09:32.214 --> 01:09:34.006
Aah!

01:09:34.091 --> 01:09:35.425
Aah!

01:09:43.225 --> 01:09:44.143
Barton?

01:09:56.989 --> 01:09:58.657
Barton, are you all right?

01:09:58.740 --> 01:09:59.740
I'm fine, thanks.

01:09:59.741 --> 01:10:00.659
You sure?

01:10:00.742 --> 01:10:01.827
No! No.

01:12:15.419 --> 01:12:17.588
Barton. Are you all right?

01:12:17.671 --> 01:12:19.631
No. Can I come in?

01:12:19.715 --> 01:12:21.592
Let's go to your room.

01:12:21.675 --> 01:12:24.595
Charlie, I'm in trouble.
You got to help me.

01:12:24.678 --> 01:12:26.597
Get a grip on yourself, brother.

01:12:26.680 --> 01:12:29.600
Whatever the problem is,
we can sort it out.

01:12:29.683 --> 01:12:32.185
Charlie, I'm in trouble.
Something horrible's happened.

01:12:32.186 --> 01:12:34.104
I got to call the police.

01:12:34.188 --> 01:12:37.107
Will you stay with me
till they get here?

01:12:37.191 --> 01:12:40.235
Don't worry about it.
We can work it out.

01:12:40.319 --> 01:12:42.613
Before you go in...
I didn't do this.

01:12:42.696 --> 01:12:45.616
I don't know how it happened, but...

01:12:45.699 --> 01:12:46.992
I didn't.

01:12:47.075 --> 01:12:49.286
I want you to know that.

01:12:56.084 --> 01:12:57.127
Okay.

01:13:03.634 --> 01:13:04.718
Ohhh!

01:13:09.807 --> 01:13:10.766
Oh...

01:13:18.774 --> 01:13:19.858
Oh...

01:13:24.321 --> 01:13:26.782
Jesus, Barton,
what the hell is this?

01:13:26.824 --> 01:13:28.325
What are we going to do?

01:13:28.408 --> 01:13:29.408
Call the police.

01:13:29.409 --> 01:13:30.452
Hold on.

01:13:30.536 --> 01:13:31.870
I didn't do this.

01:13:31.954 --> 01:13:33.455
I did not do this!

01:13:33.539 --> 01:13:34.414
Hold on!

01:13:34.498 --> 01:13:35.582
Stop.

01:13:35.624 --> 01:13:38.168
Take a deep breath.
Tell me what happened.

01:13:38.252 --> 01:13:41.046
I passed out! I don't know!
Won't the police...

01:13:41.129 --> 01:13:43.173
Stop with the police!
Wake up!

01:13:43.257 --> 01:13:45.467
This looks bad!
They hang people for this!

01:13:45.551 --> 01:13:48.554
But I didn't do it.
Don't you believe me?

01:13:48.637 --> 01:13:51.890
I believe you! I know you!
Why should the police?

01:13:53.809 --> 01:13:54.852
Did you...

01:13:56.103 --> 01:13:58.021
Barton, between you and me,

01:13:58.105 --> 01:14:00.274
did you have sexual intercourse?

01:14:03.110 --> 01:14:04.945
Jesus, they can tell that.

01:14:05.028 --> 01:14:08.115
Got to believe me!

01:14:08.198 --> 01:14:10.659
They got to have mercy!

01:14:10.701 --> 01:14:12.161
You're in pictures, Barton.

01:14:12.202 --> 01:14:14.580
Even if they cleared you eventually,

01:14:14.663 --> 01:14:16.165
this would ruin you.

01:14:18.750 --> 01:14:19.668
Come on.

01:14:19.751 --> 01:14:21.295
Wait in the bathroom.

01:14:43.901 --> 01:14:48.030
Oh, Lord.
Oh, Lordy. Oh, my Lord.

01:14:48.113 --> 01:14:51.033
Oh, my Lord.

01:14:52.868 --> 01:14:53.952
Ooh!

01:15:05.923 --> 01:15:07.716
You passed out.

01:15:09.801 --> 01:15:10.968
Where's Audrey?

01:15:10.969 --> 01:15:12.387
She's dead, Barton!

01:15:12.471 --> 01:15:15.015
She's dead, if that was her name!

01:15:15.098 --> 01:15:18.227
You got to act
as if nothing has happened.

01:15:18.310 --> 01:15:20.729
Put this totally out of your head.

01:15:20.813 --> 01:15:24.066
Your play is to go about
your business as usual.

01:15:24.149 --> 01:15:27.361
Give us some time
to sort this out.

01:15:36.703 --> 01:15:39.414
Bart!
So happy to see ya!

01:15:40.499 --> 01:15:42.793
Sit. Talk.
Relax for a minute.

01:15:42.876 --> 01:15:44.294
Then talk.

01:15:44.378 --> 01:15:45.462
Drink?

01:15:45.546 --> 01:15:47.089
Uh...

01:15:47.172 --> 01:15:48.298
yeah.

01:15:49.758 --> 01:15:50.758
Rye whiskey?

01:15:50.759 --> 01:15:53.095
Boy, you writers.
Work hard, play hard.

01:15:53.178 --> 01:15:55.055
That's what I hear, anyway.
Lou!

01:15:55.097 --> 01:15:59.476
Anyway, Ben Geisler tells me things
are going along great.

01:15:59.560 --> 01:16:01.937
Says we got a real winner
in this one.

01:16:02.020 --> 01:16:04.439
I'll tell you something.
I'm counting on it.

01:16:04.523 --> 01:16:07.234
I've taken an interest.
Nothing to fear, mind you.

01:16:07.317 --> 01:16:09.236
Hardly seems necessary in your case...

01:16:09.278 --> 01:16:11.738
a writer,
a storyteller of your stature.

01:16:11.780 --> 01:16:14.241
Give it to me
in bold strokes, Bart.

01:16:14.283 --> 01:16:15.909
Give me the broad outlines.

01:16:15.951 --> 01:16:18.453
I'm in the audience,
the lights go down,

01:16:18.495 --> 01:16:19.913
Capitol logo comes up.

01:16:19.955 --> 01:16:21.874
You're on, huh?

01:16:25.627 --> 01:16:26.920
Yeah.

01:16:26.962 --> 01:16:28.630
Uh... okay.

01:16:28.797 --> 01:16:29.923
Huh?

01:16:31.633 --> 01:16:33.093
Well, uh...

01:16:34.261 --> 01:16:35.637
we... we fade in...

01:16:35.721 --> 01:16:37.264
Uh-huh.

01:16:39.183 --> 01:16:42.269
It's... It's a tenement building
on the Lower East Side.

01:16:42.352 --> 01:16:44.313
Great!
He's poor, this wrestler.

01:16:44.354 --> 01:16:45.939
He's had to struggle, huh?

01:16:47.941 --> 01:16:49.192
And then...

01:16:49.193 --> 01:16:50.277
Uh-huh?

01:16:50.360 --> 01:16:52.029
Well, uh...

01:16:54.656 --> 01:16:56.783
Can I be honest, Mr. Lipnick?

01:16:56.825 --> 01:16:59.786
Can you?
Jesus, you damn well better be!

01:16:59.828 --> 01:17:02.206
If I wasn't honest
in my business dealings...

01:17:02.289 --> 01:17:04.208
Well, you can't always be honest,

01:17:04.291 --> 01:17:06.627
not with the sharks
swimming around this town.

01:17:06.710 --> 01:17:08.170
If I'd been totally honest,

01:17:08.212 --> 01:17:10.172
I wouldn't be near this pool

01:17:10.255 --> 01:17:11.673
unless I was cleaning it.

01:17:11.757 --> 01:17:14.593
But that's no reason
for you not to be.

01:17:14.676 --> 01:17:17.012
Honest, I mean.
Not cleaning the pool.

01:17:20.057 --> 01:17:21.141
Oh.

01:17:22.893 --> 01:17:23.977
Uh-huh.

01:17:30.734 --> 01:17:32.694
To be honest, uh...

01:17:32.736 --> 01:17:34.196
I'm never really comfortable

01:17:34.238 --> 01:17:36.240
discussing work in progress.

01:17:36.323 --> 01:17:39.159
I got it all worked out in my head,

01:17:39.243 --> 01:17:42.788
but sometimes,
if you force it into words...

01:17:42.871 --> 01:17:44.873
prematurely...

01:17:44.957 --> 01:17:46.375
uh, the wrong words...

01:17:46.416 --> 01:17:47.876
Well, your meaning changes,

01:17:47.918 --> 01:17:52.172
and it changes in your own mind,
and you never get it back,

01:17:52.256 --> 01:17:56.135
so I'd... I'd just as soon
not talk about it.

01:18:01.265 --> 01:18:03.225
Mr. Fink... never mind me.

01:18:03.308 --> 01:18:05.644
Never mind how long
I've been in pictures.

01:18:05.727 --> 01:18:07.312
Mr. Lipnick's been in pictures

01:18:07.396 --> 01:18:09.189
about since they was invented.

01:18:09.231 --> 01:18:10.649
He practically invented them.

01:18:10.732 --> 01:18:12.276
I think if he's interested

01:18:12.359 --> 01:18:15.154
in what one of
his contract employees is doing,

01:18:15.237 --> 01:18:18.073
that employee
should be able to tell him

01:18:18.157 --> 01:18:21.702
if he wants to stay an employee.

01:18:21.743 --> 01:18:24.705
Right now,
the contents of your head

01:18:24.746 --> 01:18:27.374
are the property
of Capitol Pictures.

01:18:28.584 --> 01:18:30.169
If I was you...

01:18:30.252 --> 01:18:31.670
I would speak up.

01:18:31.753 --> 01:18:33.839
And pretty goddamn fast.

01:18:37.259 --> 01:18:43.724
You lousy kike...
son of a bitch.

01:18:43.765 --> 01:18:46.059
You're telling this man...
this artist...

01:18:46.101 --> 01:18:47.603
what to do?

01:18:47.644 --> 01:18:49.021
Mr. Lipnick, I...

01:18:49.104 --> 01:18:50.647
He creates for a living!

01:18:50.731 --> 01:18:53.775
Thank him, you son of a bitch,
or you're fired!

01:18:53.859 --> 01:18:56.278
Mr. Lipnick,
that's really not necessary.

01:18:56.361 --> 01:18:59.072
Get down on your knees,
you son of a bitch!

