Honest, I'm not.

01:42:12.883 --> 01:42:16.470
Most guys I just feel sorry for.

01:42:16.553 --> 01:42:18.472
It tears me up inside

01:42:18.555 --> 01:42:21.475
to think about what
they're going through,

01:42:21.558 --> 01:42:23.977
how trapped they are.

01:42:25.062 --> 01:42:27.022
I understand it.

01:42:28.148 --> 01:42:29.983
I feel for them.

01:42:32.528 --> 01:42:35.489
So I try and help them out.

01:42:35.531 --> 01:42:36.782
Jesus.

01:42:38.784 --> 01:42:39.827
Yeah.

01:42:39.910 --> 01:42:41.578
Yeah.

01:42:41.662 --> 01:42:44.081
I know what it feels like

01:42:44.164 --> 01:42:46.583
when things get all balled up

01:42:46.667 --> 01:42:48.085
at the head office.

01:42:48.168 --> 01:42:50.754
They put you through hell, Barton.

01:42:52.172 --> 01:42:54.675
So I help people out.

01:42:57.177 --> 01:43:01.265
I just wish someone
would do as much for me.

01:43:02.850 --> 01:43:05.936
Jesus, it's hot.

01:43:09.648 --> 01:43:11.525
Sometimes it gets so hot

01:43:11.608 --> 01:43:15.154
I want to crawl
right out of my skin.

01:43:15.195 --> 01:43:18.490
But, Charlie, why me?

01:43:18.532 --> 01:43:19.658
Why...

01:43:19.700 --> 01:43:23.328
Because you don't listen!

01:43:31.170 --> 01:43:32.880
Jesus.

01:43:32.963 --> 01:43:34.590
I'm dripping again.

01:43:37.676 --> 01:43:40.012
Come on, Barton,

01:43:40.053 --> 01:43:43.182
you think you know pain?

01:43:44.558 --> 01:43:47.853
You think I made your life hell?

01:43:49.188 --> 01:43:50.564
Look around this dump.

01:43:50.647 --> 01:43:53.609
You're just a tourist
with a typewriter.

01:43:53.692 --> 01:43:56.570
I live here.
Don't you understand that?

01:44:03.368 --> 01:44:06.330
And you come into my home...

01:44:08.457 --> 01:44:10.375
and you complain

01:44:10.417 --> 01:44:14.379
that I'm making too much noise.

01:44:25.933 --> 01:44:27.893
I'm sorry.

01:44:34.983 --> 01:44:37.110
Don't be.

01:45:24.700 --> 01:45:27.786
I'll be next door
if you need me.

01:45:31.790 --> 01:45:33.125
Oh...

01:45:33.167 --> 01:45:35.669
I dropped in on
your folks in New York.

01:45:35.752 --> 01:45:38.755
And Uncle Maury.

01:45:38.839 --> 01:45:40.215
Good people.

01:45:46.555 --> 01:45:49.516
By the way,
that package I gave you...

01:45:49.558 --> 01:45:51.101
I lied.

01:45:51.185 --> 01:45:53.187
It isn't mine.

01:46:57.251 --> 01:46:58.585
Fink.

01:46:58.669 --> 01:47:00.087
Samuel or Lillian Fink.

01:47:00.170 --> 01:47:01.588
85 Fulton Street.

01:47:01.672 --> 01:47:03.132
Or Uncle Maury.

01:47:03.215 --> 01:47:06.051
I understand that,
but there's still no answer.

01:47:06.093 --> 01:47:07.052
Mr. Fink?

01:47:07.094 --> 01:47:10.055
Shall I check for trouble
on the line?

01:47:15.936 --> 01:47:18.188
Fink.

01:47:18.272 --> 01:47:19.606
Mr. Lipnick.

01:47:19.690 --> 01:47:22.109
Colonel Lipnick...
if you don't mind.

01:47:22.192 --> 01:47:23.443
Sit down.

01:47:23.527 --> 01:47:25.736
I was commissioned yesterday
in the army reserve.

01:47:25.737 --> 01:47:28.448
Henry Morgenthau arranged it.
Dear friend.

01:47:28.532 --> 01:47:30.450
Congratulations.

01:47:30.492 --> 01:47:31.701
It hasn't officially
gone through yet.

01:47:31.702 --> 01:47:33.120
Had wardrobe whip this up.

01:47:33.203 --> 01:47:35.164
Got to pull teeth
to get anything done.

01:47:35.247 --> 01:47:37.458
Can understand
red tape in peacetime,

01:47:37.541 --> 01:47:39.626
but now it's all-out warfare
against theJaps.

01:47:39.710 --> 01:47:42.421
They'd love to see me
sit this one out.

01:47:42.463 --> 01:47:44.965
Yes, sir.
They, uh...

01:47:45.048 --> 01:47:48.677
Anyway, I had Lou
read your script for me.

01:47:48.760 --> 01:47:51.180
I got to tell you, Fink...

01:47:51.263 --> 01:47:52.890
it won't wash.

01:47:52.973 --> 01:47:54.056
With all due respect,

01:47:54.057 --> 01:47:56.310
I think it's
the best work I've done.

01:47:56.393 --> 01:47:57.685
Don't gas me, Fink.

01:47:57.686 --> 01:48:01.648
If your opinion mattered,
I'd let you run the studio.

01:48:01.732 --> 01:48:04.275
The lunatics aren't going to run
this particular asylum.

01:48:04.276 --> 01:48:07.029
Let's put a stop
to that rumor right now.

01:48:07.154 --> 01:48:09.281
Yes, sir.

01:48:09.323 --> 01:48:10.908
Had to call Beery this morning,

01:48:10.991 --> 01:48:13.660
tell him we were pushing
the picture back.

01:48:13.702 --> 01:48:15.621
After all I told him about quality,

01:48:15.662 --> 01:48:16.955
about that Barton Fink feeling,

01:48:17.039 --> 01:48:18.415
how disappointed we were.

01:48:18.499 --> 01:48:21.418
Wally was heartbroken.
The man was devastated.

01:48:21.502 --> 01:48:23.921
I didn't actually call him.
Lou did.

01:48:24.004 --> 01:48:26.715
That's a fair description,
isn't it, Lou?

01:48:26.799 --> 01:48:27.840
Yes, Colonel.

01:48:27.841 --> 01:48:31.303
I could take you
through it step-by-step,

01:48:31.345 --> 01:48:33.305
explaining why
your story stinks,

01:48:33.347 --> 01:48:35.766
but I won't insult
your intelligence.

01:48:35.849 --> 01:48:36.891
Well, all right.

01:48:36.892 --> 01:48:39.269
First of all,
this is a wrestling picture.

01:48:39.353 --> 01:48:42.606
The audience wants to see action,
adventure, wrestling.

01:48:42.689 --> 01:48:45.984
They don't want to see a guy
wrestling with his soul.

01:48:46.068 --> 01:48:47.611
All right, some for the critics.

01:48:47.694 --> 01:48:50.155
You make it the carrot
that wags the dog.

01:48:50.197 --> 01:48:52.032
Too much,
they head for the exits.

01:48:52.115 --> 01:48:55.035
There's plenty of poetry
inside that ring, Fink.

01:48:55.118 --> 01:48:57.329
Look at Hell 10 Feet Square.

01:48:57.371 --> 01:48:58.664
Blood, Sweat, and Canvas.

01:48:58.705 --> 01:48:59.956
Blood, Sweat, and Canvas.

01:48:59.957 --> 01:49:02.918
These are big movies,
Fink, about big men.

01:49:03.001 --> 01:49:03.877
In tights!

01:49:03.961 --> 01:49:06.380
Both physically
and mentally...

01:49:06.421 --> 01:49:08.173
especially physically.

01:49:08.215 --> 01:49:10.843
We don't put Wally Beery
in a fruity movie about suffering.

01:49:10.884 --> 01:49:13.762
I thought we were
together on that.

01:49:15.055 --> 01:49:17.391
I'm sorry if I let you down.

01:49:17.474 --> 01:49:19.518
You didn't let me down
or even Lou.

01:49:19.560 --> 01:49:22.354
We don't live or die
by what you scribble.

01:49:22.396 --> 01:49:23.689
You let Ben Geisler down.

01:49:23.730 --> 01:49:25.691
He liked you,
trusted you.

01:49:25.732 --> 01:49:27.734
That's why he's gone.
He's fired.

01:49:27.776 --> 01:49:29.695
That man had a big heart.

01:49:29.736 --> 01:49:31.028
You fucked him.

01:49:31.029 --> 01:49:33.198
He tried to convince me
to fire you, too,

01:49:33.240 --> 01:49:34.700
but that'd be too easy.

01:49:34.741 --> 01:49:36.702
You're under contract.
You'll stay that way.

01:49:36.743 --> 01:49:39.245
Anything you write is
property of Capitol Pictures.

01:49:39.246 --> 01:49:42.207
Capitol Pictures won't produce
anything you write...

01:49:42.249 --> 01:49:44.751
not until you
grow up a little.

01:49:44.835 --> 01:49:47.254
You ain't no writer, Fink.

01:49:47.296 --> 01:49:49.756
You're a goddamn write-off.

01:49:51.467 --> 01:49:54.761
I... I tried to show you...

01:49:54.803 --> 01:49:56.221
something beautiful.

01:49:58.265 --> 01:50:00.267
Something about all of us.

01:50:00.309 --> 01:50:01.393
I...

01:50:01.435 --> 01:50:05.230
You arrogant
son of a bitch.

01:50:05.272 --> 01:50:07.649
You think
you're the only writer

01:50:07.733 --> 01:50:10.194
that can give me
that Barton Fink feeling?

01:50:10.277 --> 01:50:12.779
I got 20 writers
under contract

01:50:12.863 --> 01:50:15.741
I can ask for
a Fink-type thing from!

01:50:15.782 --> 01:50:17.159
You swell-headed hypocrite.

01:50:17.242 --> 01:50:18.494
You don't get it.

01:50:18.577 --> 01:50:19.911
You think the whole world

01:50:19.912 --> 01:50:21.497
revolves around
whatever rattles

01:50:21.580 --> 01:50:24.666
inside that little
kike head of yours.

01:50:24.750 --> 01:50:27.336
Get him out of my sight, Lou!

01:50:27.419 --> 01:50:29.171
I want him in town, though.

01:50:29.254 --> 01:50:30.714
He's still under contract.

01:50:30.798 --> 01:50:34.968
I want you in town
and out of my sight.

01:50:35.010 --> 01:50:37.179
Now, get lost.

01:50:37.262 --> 01:50:38.847
There's a war on.

01:51:37.072 --> 01:51:39.491
It's a beautiful day.

01:51:39.533 --> 01:51:40.659
Huh?

01:51:46.874 --> 01:51:49.835
I said it's a beautiful day.

01:51:49.877 --> 01:51:51.211
Yes.

01:51:51.295 --> 01:51:53.046
It is.

01:51:55.716 --> 01:51:57.676
What's in the box?

01:51:59.595 --> 01:52:01.472
I don't know.

01:52:02.764 --> 01:52:04.558
Isn't it yours?

01:52:09.730 --> 01:52:11.815
I don't know.

01:52:17.738 --> 01:52:19.948
You're very beautiful.

01:52:24.745 --> 01:52:26.830
Are you in pictures?

01:52:28.081 --> 01:52:30.000
Don't be silly.

